<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="N" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Neptune" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Neptune,</orth> the god of the ocean and the seas: <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.28" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.2.174" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 2, 174</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.256" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 256</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 2.2.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 2, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.1.119" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 1, 119</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.7.139" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 7, 139</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.1.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 1, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V Prol.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. per 5.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V Prol.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. per 5.1.17" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 17</bibl>. == the sea: <cit><quote>the fire and cracks of sulphurous roaring the most mighty N. seem to besiege,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.204" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 204</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>chase the ebbing N.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.35.204" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 35</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>sat with me on --'s yellow sands,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.126" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 126</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.392" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 392</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 5.1.154" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 1, 154</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.2.34" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 2, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.63" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.1.51" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 1, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.4.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 4, 78</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.166" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 2, 166</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.14.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 14, 58</bibl>. Per. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.0." default="NO" valid="yes">III Prol. 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.3.36" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 36</bibl>.
